{{Arabic alphabet}}
{{Arabic-script sidebar|Persian}}

'''Keheh''' is a letter of [[Arabic script]], used to write {{IPAblink|kʰ}} in [[Sindhi language|Sindhi]]. It is equivalent to <big>{{lang|sa|[[ख]]}}</big> in Sindhi's [[Devanagari]] orthography.

{{Arabic alphabet shapes|ک}}

In [[Arabic language|Arabic]], <big>{{script/Arabic|ک}}</big> and <big>{{script/Arabic|ڪ}}</big> are both considered variant forms of [[kāf]], but in [[Sindhi language|Sindhi]] they are differentiated: <big>{{script/Arabic|ک}}</big> is used consistently for {{IPA|/kʰ/}}, and <big>{{script/Arabic|ڪ}}</big> for {{IPA|/k/}}. This is similar to the history of [[I]] and [[J]], and of [[U]] and [[V]], in the [[Latin alphabet]].

{{Arabic alphabet shapes|ڪ}}

{{DEFAULTSORT:Keheh}}
[[Category:Arabic letters]]

This glyph may not rendered or displayed as ک in Apple users’ devices. That’s because Apple is using various fonts to render Arabic text. It will also not rendered if there’s languages displayed as [[Nasta’liq]] in the Language list in Apple devices.
{{arabic-script-stub}}

{{SpecialChars}}
{{Arabic alphabet}}
'''ݪ''' ([[Unicode]] name: Arabic Letter Lam With Bar, code point U+076A) is an additional letter of the [[Arabic script]], derived from [[lām]] (ل) with the addition of a [[bar (diacritic)|bar]]. It is not used in the [[Arabic alphabet]] itself, but is used in [[Punjabi language|Punjabi]] and [[Marwari language|Marwari]] to represent a [[retroflex lateral flap]], and in [[Kalami language|Kalami]] to represent a [[voiceless lateral fricative]], {{IPAblink|ɬ}}).

{{DEFAULTSORT:Lam with bar}}
[[Category:Arabic letters]]


{{arabic-script-stub}}

{{distinguish|text=[[Rā with two dots above]] (ڗ)}}
{{SpecialChars}}
{{Arabic alphabet}}
'''ݫ''' ([[Unicode]] name: Arabic Letter Reh With Two Dots Vertically Above) is an additional letter of the [[Arabic script]], derived from '''rāʾ''' (ر) with the addition of two [[dot (diacritic)|dots]] above the letter. It is not used in the [[Arabic alphabet]] itself, but is used in [[Ormuri language|Ormuri]] to represent a [[voiced alveolo-palatal fricative]], {{IPAblink|ʑ}}), as well as in [[Torwali language|Torwali]].

{{DEFAULTSORT:Ra with two dots vertically above}}
[[Category:Arabic letters]]


{{arabic-script-stub}}

{{SpecialChars}}
{{Arabic alphabet}}
'''ݭ''' is an additional letter of the [[Arabic script]], derived from [[sīn]] (س) with the addition of two vertically aligned [[dot (diacritic)|dots]] above the letter. It is not used in the [[Arabic alphabet]] itself, but is used in [[Kalami language|Kalami]] to represent a [[voiceless retroflex fricative]], {{IPAblink|ʂ}}), and in [[Ormuri language|Ormuri]] to represent a [[voiceless alveolo-palatal fricative]], {{IPA|[ɕ]}}).


[[Category:Arabic letters|S]]


{{arabic-script-stub}}

{{SpecialChars}}
{{Arabic alphabet}}
'''ݜ''' ([[Unicode]] name: Arabic Letter Seen With Four Dots Above) is an additional letter of the [[Arabic script]], derived from [[sīn]] (ﺱ) with the addition of four [[dot (diacritic)|dots]] or two horizontal lines above the letter. It is not used in the [[Arabic alphabet]] itself, but is used in [[Shina language|Shina]] to represent [[voiceless retroflex fricative]], {{IPAblink|ʂ}}.

{{DEFAULTSORT:Sin with four dots above}}
[[Category:Arabic letters]]


{{arabic-script-stub}}

{{Unreferenced|date=September 2009}}
{{Arabic script sidebar|Urdu}}

'''Ṭē''' is an additional letter of the [[Perso-Arabic alphabet]], derived from [[tāʾ|te]] ({{lang|ar|ت}}) by replacing the dots with a small [[ṭāʾ|t&#x324;oʾe]] ({{lang|ar|ط}}). It is not used in the [[Arabic alphabet]] itself, but is used to represent {{IPAblink|ʈ}} in [[Urdu]]. The small t̤oʾe diactric is used to indicate a [[retroflex consonant]] in Urdu. It is the fifth letter of the [[Urdu alphabet]]. Its [[Abjad]] value is considered to be 400. In Urdu, this letter may also be called ‘heavy t’ or ‘Indian t’. In [[Devanagari]], this consonant is rendered using ‘[[ट]]’.

{{Arabic alphabet shapes|ٹ}}

Some layout engines do not properly generate medial and final forms (which should look like <span style="font-size:2em;padding:0 0.1em">{{lang|ur|{{nq|ـٹـ}}}}</span> and <span style="font-size:2em;padding:0 0.1em">{{lang|ur|{{nq|ﭨ}}}}</span>) and will render the isolate form <span style="font-size:2em;padding:0 0.1em">{{lang|ur|{{nq|ٹ}}}}</span>, without joining.

{{DEFAULTSORT:Te}}
[[Category:Arabic letters]]


{{arabic-script-stub}}

{{Unreferenced|date=March 2009}}
{{Arabic alphabet}}
'''Ṭhē''' is an additional letter of the [[Arabic script]]. It has the basic shape of [[tāʼ]] (<big>'''ت'''</big>), but with vertical dots, rather than [[Horizontal plane|horizontal]]. It is not used in the [[Arabic alphabet]] itself, but is used to represent an [[aspiration (phonetics)|aspirated]] {{IPAblink|ʈ|ʈʰ}} in [[Sindhi language|Sindhi]], a language mainly spoken in [[Pakistan]].

{{Arabic alphabet shapes|ٺ}}

Sindhi is also written in [[Devanagari]], where the corresponding letter is [[ठ]].

{{DEFAULTSORT:The}}
[[Category:Arabic letters]]


