== Gaf with single dot below ==

{{big|{{script/Arabic|ࢴ}}}} is derived from a variant form ({{big|{{script/Arabic|ك}}}}) of kāf with the addition of a [[dot (diacritic)|dot]] below. It is not used in the [[Arabic language]] itself, but is used in the [[Pegon script]] of [[Languages of Indonesia|Indonesian languages]] to represent a [[voiced velar stop]] {{IPAslink|ɡ}}. This also used in [[Arwi alphabet]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.unicode.org/L2/L2013/13130-arwi.pdf|author=Roozbeh Pournader, Google|title=Proposal to encode three Arabic characters for Arwi|date=June 24, 2013}}</ref>
